messages.content: 9-1-1, what's your emergency?
Ronald 911 with the location of the emergency.
This is Callow. We're at the Best Western off of 114. Someone has been shot in the neck. They're going to need medical assistance.
Go ahead, sir.
Yes, sir.
Let me get Denton County on the line to get you an ambulance. What room are they in?
Sir, what room are they in?
They're not in a room, we're out at the pool right now. The pool area.
Denton County 911.
Yes, ma'am. This is Brooke up at the transfer. We need an ambulance. We have a shooting at the Best Western.
Sir, what's the address there?
Ma'am, I'm not sure of the exact address. It's 377 and 114.
Okay, what's going on there, sir?
I'm an off-duty officer. Somebody got a hold of my gun. It's 801 West Byron Nelson.
801 West Byron Nelson?
I'm not sure. It's 377 and 114, but somebody got a hold of my gun and shot somebody.
Okay, so somebody took your weapon and shot somebody else in the neck?
Yes, ma'am.
Okay. Where's the weapon at now, sir?
I have it in my custody.
Okay, you have it in your custody. Where's the person that did the shooting?
He is right here next to me. It's... It's fine. He didn't understand it was an off-duty weapon.
I have an ambulance on the way. What is your name, sir?
Okay, what's going on? There's an argument.
Why, God! Why!
Sir, who is yelling?
Hello? Hello, who did you have me call?
Sir, who is yelling?
Sir?
Sir?
Yes, ma'am. I need to talk to you. I don't need to talk to him. The person that is shot.
The person that was shot, where are they?
She's right on the ground and a nurse is doing CPR on her.
CPR is in progress?
Yes, ma'am.
